    <text id="B0049T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Annie Branham's letter to Jackson alludes to a dispute with her servant, Joshua,
                    over the amount owed to him in wages.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    
                    <salute>Mr Jackson</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I am owing <unclear>Joshua</unclear> $24.90 balance on services rendered. He is
                    owing me $20 for children's board and $3 for Table ware broken by self &amp;
                    children.</p>

                <p>I did not send for you to come to my house to settle with Joshua, but told him
                    that you said you would attend to it today &amp; that you would be round
                    after a while--about dinner time.</p>


                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>Annie E. Branham</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
